[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":340},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F17\u002Fscss-handbook-2-variables\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F17\u002Fscss-handbook-2-variables\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F17\u002Fscss-handbook-2-variables\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F17\u002Fscss-handbook-2-variables\u002F":317,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F17\u002Fscss-handbook-2-variables\u002F":326},"\u002FSCSS\u002F20190417\u002F2961076508\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":8,"body":9,"category":301,"date":302,"description":20,"extension":303,"lang":304,"meta":305,"navigation":306,"path":307,"readingMinutes":308,"seo":309,"standalone":310,"stem":311,"tags":312,"tldr":314,"updated":314,"url":315,"__hash__":316},"content\u002Fen\u002FSCSS\u002Fscss-handbook-2-variables.md","SCSS Handbook (2) — Variables ($)","9610765082","\u002Fscss\u002F20190417\u002F2961076508\u002F",{"type":10,"value":11,"toc":293},"minimark",[12,17,21,25,45,48,55,66,71,80,84,87,90,93,98,105,110,113,119,129,134,140,146,162,167,170,175,178,184,187,190,195,201,208,212,215],[13,14,16],"h2",{"id":15},"intro","Intro",[18,19,20],"p",{},"From this post on we won't talk about SASS — let's focus on the SCSS basics.",[13,22,24],{"id":23},"whats-a-variable-can-you-eat-it","What's a variable? Can you eat it?",[18,26,27,28,32,33,36,37,40,41,44],{},"The most convenient thing in SCSS is variables. SCSS uses the ",[29,30,31],"code",{},"$"," sign for variables:\n",[29,34,35],{},"$variableName: color, number, or string",".\nFor example: ",[29,38,39],{},"$black: #ec0f0f","\n(",[29,42,43],{},"#ec0f0f"," is red.)",[18,46,47],{},"Let's quickly sketch a box as usual to see this in action.",[18,49,50],{},[51,52],"img",{"alt":53,"src":54},"image","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fxc6Engl.png",[18,56,57,58,61,62,65],{},"In the image, I stored a color in the ",[29,59,60],{},"$red"," variable and used it as the ",[29,63,64],{},"background-color",".",[18,67,68],{},[51,69],{"alt":53,"src":70},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FTSP5cXS.png",[18,72,73],{},[74,75,79],"a",{"href":76,"rel":77},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FqggPNr",[78],"nofollow","CodePen",[13,81,83],{"id":82},"whats-the-upside","What's the upside?",[18,85,86],{},"Some folks will ask — what's the benefit of this?",[18,88,89],{},"Because plain CSS often runs to hundreds or thousands of lines, and some colors get reused all over the place. When you need to change a color, it gets really tedious. Plus, you don't have to memorize hex codes.",[18,91,92],{},"Let's actually try it. First, add 5 boxes:",[18,94,95],{},[51,96],{"alt":53,"src":97},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F8NY3pRW.png",[18,99,100,101,104],{},"Then write the 5 corresponding boxes in SCSS, with ",[29,102,103],{},"background-color: $red",":",[18,106,107],{},[51,108],{"alt":53,"src":109},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F15Vdbuz.png",[18,111,112],{},"Now we have 5 red boxes:",[18,114,115],{},[74,116,79],{"href":117,"rel":118},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FzeeEKq",[78],[18,120,121,122,125,126,128],{},"To change all five ",[29,123,124],{},".box"," colors before, we'd have to edit each one individually. With SCSS variables, just update ",[29,127,60],{}," at the top:",[18,130,131],{},[51,132],{"alt":53,"src":133},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FMzG5JCU.png",[18,135,136,137,139],{},"The result — every class using ",[29,138,60],{}," becomes the new color:",[18,141,142],{},[74,143,79],{"href":144,"rel":145},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FpGGWEM",[78],[18,147,148,149,152,153,152,156,152,159,104],{},"We can also push numeric values to variables to speed up box production. Let me add a few: ",[29,150,151],{},"$box-width",", ",[29,154,155],{},"$box-height",[29,157,158],{},"$mb-1: 5px",[29,160,161],{},"$mb-2: 10px",[18,163,164],{},[51,165],{"alt":53,"src":166},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F2B55ffH.png",[18,168,169],{},"Then use them in CSS properties:",[18,171,172],{},[51,173],{"alt":53,"src":174},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fusfhqfn.png",[18,176,177],{},"Result:",[18,179,180],{},[74,181,79],{"href":182,"rel":183},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FJxxrEW",[78],[18,185,186],{},"I'm sure you can see the power of SCSS variables. When building websites we'd often tweak the font-family, so I put fonts into variables too.",[18,188,189],{},"Before applying a custom font:",[18,191,192],{},[51,193],{"alt":53,"src":194},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FlvqBdLB.png",[18,196,197,198],{},"Using an SCSS variable to load fonts — here I use the system default:\n",[51,199],{"alt":53,"src":200},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FYVBU4w3.png",[18,202,203,204],{},"The image might not show the difference clearly, so try it yourself!\n",[74,205,79],{"href":206,"rel":207},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FgqqGWd",[78],[13,209,211],{"id":210},"system-default-fonts","System default fonts",[18,213,214],{},"Here's a table of system default fonts. Heads up — don't type out \"微軟正黑體\" directly because it can occasionally cause weird issues.",[216,217,218,238],"table",{},[219,220,221],"thead",{},[222,223,224,229,232,235],"tr",{},[225,226,228],"th",{"align":227},"center","System",[225,230,231],{"align":227},"System default",[225,233,234],{"align":227},"English font",[225,236,237],{"align":227},"CJK font",[239,240,241,255,269,280],"tbody",{},[222,242,243,247,250,252],{},[244,245,246],"td",{"align":227},"Windows",[244,248,249],{"align":227},"-",[244,251],{"align":227},[244,253,254],{"align":227},"Microsoft JhengHei \u002F 微軟正黑體",[222,256,257,260,263,266],{},[244,258,259],{"align":227},"Mac OS",[244,261,262],{"align":227},"-apple-system",[244,264,265],{"align":227},"San Francisco",[244,267,268],{"align":227},"PingFang",[222,270,271,274,276,278],{},[244,272,273],{"align":227},"iOS",[244,275,262],{"align":227},[244,277,265],{"align":227},[244,279,268],{"align":227},[222,281,282,285,287,290],{},[244,283,284],{"align":227},"Android",[244,286,249],{"align":227},[244,288,289],{"align":227},"Roboto",[244,291,292],{"align":227},"Droidsansfallback",{"title":294,"searchDepth":295,"depth":295,"links":296},"",2,[297,298,299,300],{"id":15,"depth":295,"text":16},{"id":23,"depth":295,"text":24},{"id":82,"depth":295,"text":83},{"id":210,"depth":295,"text":211},"SCSS","2019-04-17 12:45:50","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002Fscss-handbook-2-variables","2",{"title":6,"description":20},false,"en\u002FSCSS\u002Fscss-handbook-2-variables",[301,313],"SCSS Handbook",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F17\u002Fscss-handbook-2-variables\u002F","GLeDqJM6H-UDE6tHPLjDbum26yIMYMsNzzvgRWhGnR0",{"newer":318,"older":322},{"url":319,"title":320,"date":321},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F18\u002Fjavascript-merge-array-object-properties\u002F","How I Merged Array Object Properties in JavaScript (and Burned 4 Hours Doing It)","2019-04-18 16:00:00",{"url":323,"title":324,"date":325},"\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F16\u002Fhow-to-properly-learn-frontend-or-programming\u002F","How to Properly Learn Frontend Tech or Programming Languages","2019-04-16 22:36:38",[327,332,336],{"url":328,"title":329,"date":330,"readingMinutes":331},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2025\u002F11\u002F23\u002Fsass-deprecated-import-use-forward-migration\u002F","SCSS Is Deprecating @import?!","2025-11-23 15:32:01","4",{"url":333,"title":334,"date":335,"readingMinutes":308},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F21\u002Fscss-handbook-5-mixin\u002F","SCSS Handbook (5) — mixin","2019-04-21 07:24:30",{"url":337,"title":338,"date":339,"readingMinutes":308},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F19\u002Fscss-handbook-4-import\u002F","SCSS Handbook (4) — @import","2019-04-19 17:24:30",1784013073094]